Stopped in for a drink and some breakfast before a Red Sox game one Saturday. Arrived at 10:45am and was greeted by a friendly hostess. We opted to sit at the bar and order there. The Bloody Mary I ordered was spectacular. I particularly enjoyed the salt and pepper on the rim. My wife had a Tropical Mimosa and French toast. She said is was excellent. The service was great and from our observation of the room the overall service of the restaurant and the outdoor patio was above average. All the food coming out of the kitchen looked excellent. The prices were fair and definitely lower then a couple blocks away nearer the stadium. We will return to this establishment anytime we attend a game or are in the area again.

Thornton's has been our go-to brunch place for years now. While on the outside it appears unassuming, the food they serve is of surprisingly high quality, and they pull this off with consistency. Their chicken sandwiches and the alway-on-the-menu chicken and waffles are crispy and juicy. They have a rotating brunch special that tends to be either a breakfast burrito or a Tex-Mex style dish. The hash is hearty without being overwhelming (although could do with a bit more pizzazz). At this point, I've basically tried every item on their menu, and I can personally recommend all of them. Check this place out, and order your favorite go-to brunch item to see for yourself.
